The paper discusses feature learning for challenging learning problems in domains such as speech, computer vision, and natural language processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper specifically discusses the use of score-function features for discriminative learning, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
